%% NSN-side multi-NSGW failover sequence
%% Source: crates/connector/src/multi.rs + lib.rs + tests/docker/nsd-mock/src/registry.ts
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant NSN as NSN MultiGatewayManager
    participant G1 as NSGW-1 (primary)
    participant G2 as NSGW-2 (fallback)
    participant ND as NSD

    Note over NSN,ND: Steady state: both gateways in gateway_config, strategy=LowestLatency
    NSN->>G1: WG handshake + data (active)
    NSN->>G2: WG handshake (standby, Connected)
    NSN->>NSN: health loop every 30s (multi.rs:176)

    Note over G1: G1 host crashes (UDP stops responding)
    NSN->>G1: WG keepalive
    Note over NSN: probe timeout 5s (probe_udp, lib.rs:241)
    NSN->>NSN: mark G1 Reconnecting(attempt=1)<br/>emit GatewayEvent::Reconnecting
    NSN->>NSN: select_gateway() -> G2<br/>(multi.rs:270-277)
    NSN-->>NSN: emit GatewayEvent::Connected{id=G2, transport=UDP}
    NSN->>G2: data flow cut over (no re-handshake, already Connected)

    par NSD independent detection
        ND->>G1: health probe fails
        ND-->>ND: remove G1 from gateways map
        ND-->>NSN: SSE gateway_config (without G1)
        NSN->>NSN: mark G1 Disabled
    and NSN backoff retry (if still in config)
        NSN->>G1: reconnect attempt (backoff)
        alt retry OK
            G1-->>NSN: handshake ok
            NSN->>NSN: mark G1 Connected<br/>(stays on G2 unless strategy says switch back)
        else retry exhausted
            NSN->>NSN: mark G1 Failed
        end
    end

    Note over G1: Operator restarts G1 (new keypair)
    G1->>ND: POST /api/v1/gateway/report (new pubkey)
    ND-->>NSN: SSE gateway_config with G1 again
    NSN->>NSN: mark G1 Pending -> connect()
    NSN->>G1: WG handshake (new peer entry)
    G1-->>NSN: ok -> Connected
    Note over NSN: LowestLatency re-evaluates on next LatencyUpdate
